3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Funding rates on Orderly Network calculate every hour based on the premium between perpetual and spot prices across the shared order book. The distributed architecture means funding payments flow through smart contracts on NEAR Protocol, with settlement occurring automatically across all connected frontends. Trading fees of 0.02% for makers and 0.05% for takers apply before funding calculations, impacting net arbitrage returns."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","XRP","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"XRP/USDT on Orderly Network benefits from the protocol's multi-chain accessibility, allowing arbitrageurs to compare rates across NEAR and EVM-compatible chains simultaneously. The major pair status ensures consistent volume flow through the shared liquidity layer, while hourly settlements provide frequent arbitrage windows compared to traditional 8-hour cycles."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"XRP/USDT funding rates on Orderly Network typically range from -0.1% to +0.2% hourly during normal market conditions, with extreme spikes reaching ±0.5% during high volatility periods. The shared liquidity model tends to dampen rate extremes compared to isolated DEX pools, as arbitrageurs can access the same order book through multiple frontend interfaces. Regulatory news affecting XRP often triggers 2-4 hour periods of elevated funding rates as sentiment shifts rapidly across the ecosystem. Weekend periods show reduced rate volatility due to lower institutional participation in the shared liquidity pool."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"The hourly funding cycle creates 24 daily arbitrage windows, significantly more than traditional perpetual exchanges. Cross-chain arbitrage becomes viable through Orderly's multi-chain infrastructure, allowing traders to compare XRP rates between NEAR-based and EVM-based positions simultaneously. The shared order book means rate discrepancies often persist for 15-30 minutes as different frontend users react at varying speeds to funding announcements. Optimal entry timing occurs 10-15 minutes before funding settlement when rate predictions solidify but positions haven't fully adjusted."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Orderly Network's complex architecture introduces smart contract risks across multiple chains and dependency on frontend partner stability for position management. The shared liquidity model means sudden frontend outages could temporarily limit access to positions during critical funding periods. Cross-chain bridge risks apply when moving collateral between NEAR and EVM environments, with potential delays during network congestion. Position sizing must account for the 0.05% taker fee structure, which can eliminate profits from smaller funding rate differentials below 0.1% hourly."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How does Orderly Network's shared liquidity affect XRP funding rates?","answer":"The shared order book aggregates trading activity across all connected DEX frontends, creating more stable funding rates than isolated pools. This typically results in less extreme rate swings but also fewer high-profit arbitrage opportunities."},{"question":"Can I access XRP positions on Orderly through different chains simultaneously?","answer":"Yes, Orderly's multi-chain infrastructure allows you to compare and potentially arbitrage XRP positions between NEAR and EVM-compatible chains. However, cross-chain collateral transfers may introduce timing delays and bridge risks."},{"question":"What are the optimal times for XRP funding rate arbitrage on Orderly?","answer":"With hourly settlements, opportunities arise every 60 minutes. The best entry window is typically 10-15 minutes before each hour when funding predictions are reliable but positions haven't fully adjusted to expected rates."},{"question":"How do frontend outages affect XRP funding rate strategies on Orderly?","answer":"Since Orderly operates through partner frontends, outages can temporarily limit access to position management tools. However, the shared order book continues operating, and alternative frontend access usually remains available through other partner platforms."}]}]
